# CODEOWNERS — L3 surface inventory for the current solo-maintainer repository.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  ⚠️  THIS FILE IS AN OWNERSHIP MAP, NOT AN INDEPENDENT-REVIEW GATE.
#      @zensgit is the sole developer and cannot approve its own pull requests.
#      `require_code_owner_reviews` MUST remain false while that is true.
#
#  Solo-maintainer L3 protocol:
#
#   1. An isolated critic that did not author the patch first derives the
#      load-bearing discriminators from the ratified design lock, then reviews
#      the implementation. Use a different model when available; at minimum use
#      a fresh context with no inherited implementation rationale.
#   2. The critic's findings, fail-first golden, observed-RED evidence, and final
#      reviewed head are recorded in the PR. The critic supplies evidence only;
#      it does not approve or ratify the change.
#   3. The human owner explicitly ratifies the design and authorizes the pinned
#      head. Merge and production enablement remain separate owner decisions;
#      L3 runtime ships default-off.
#
#  Do not create a second account controlled by the same person to simulate
#  independence. If a genuinely independent human reviewer is added later,
#  amend every applicable rule first and only then consider enabling
#  `require_code_owner_reviews`.
#
#  This PR changes no branch-protection setting.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Why (PRODUCT_STRATEGY.md §7.1): touching auth, authorization, customer data, an
# AI-output sink, a MODEL-RELEASE / MODEL-ACTIVATION surface, lifecycle write-back,
# or cross-system writes automatically promotes work to L3. Authors may not self-downgrade.
#
# This file exists because an unattended cadence loop authored a model-release gate
# (#509/#510/#511) and produced a FAKE-GREEN gate. §4.7 — "the author of a guard must not
# be the only author or reviewer of the discriminator that claims to prove it" — earned its
# place on the very first L3 attempt. An unattended loop cannot be author, critic, or ratifier.

# --- Model ACTIVATION membrane (L3) ------------------------------------------
# The activation boundary is CROSS-FAMILY and much broader than reload_model(): every
# module that deserializes model bytes into a running service is an activation surface.
# `torch.load(weights_only=False)` is arbitrary-code-execution on load (pickle-equivalent),
# and `pickle.load`/`pickle.loads` likewise. Verified production-reachable loaders on main:
#   pickle-classifier — src/api/v1/model.py:71 (/model/reload, ADMIN_TOKEN default "test";
#                       pickle.loads BEFORE the hash check), src/ml/classifier.py:85 (startup
#                       pickle.load, no magic/hash/opcode), :535 (hot-reload)
#   graph2d          — src/ml/vision_2d.py:136 (torch.load weights_only=False)
#   pointnet         — src/api/v1/pointcloud.py (MOUNTED /pointcloud) -> src/ml/pointnet/inference.py:108
#   part / v16 / v14 — src/ml/part_classifier.py:62,655,695 (reached via /analyze, /health)
#   hybrid           — src/ml/hybrid_classifier.py:448,476
#   history-sequence — src/ml/history_sequence_classifier.py:162 (reached via /analyze)
#   vision3d         — src/ml/vision_3d.py:196
# Latent/producer/scaffold also owned: auto_remediation.py:301 (latent rollback),
# scripts/finetune_from_feedback.py:302 (offline), src/ml/serving/* (unmounted scaffold).
/src/api/v1/model.py                  @zensgit
/src/api/v1/pointcloud.py             @zensgit
/src/ml/classifier.py                 @zensgit
/src/ml/vision_2d.py                  @zensgit
/src/ml/vision_3d.py                  @zensgit
/src/ml/part_classifier.py            @zensgit
/src/ml/hybrid_classifier.py          @zensgit
/src/ml/history_sequence_classifier.py @zensgit
/src/ml/pointnet/                     @zensgit
